answer: libbeef is a library-based implementation of the Bayesian Error Estimation Functional (BEEF), suitable for linking against by Fortran- or C-based DFT codes.

answer: The current version of libbeef is 0.1.2.

answer: More information about libbeef can be found at its homepage: https://github.com/vossjo/libbeef, or in the paper at http://dx.doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevB.85.235149.
